{"key":"processedPost-13523300","value":{"id":13523300,"first":13523259,"last":13523339,"when":1290442989,"utime":"11/22/10 06:23 PM","content":"The made in china crap for hygrometers they pass off on us now are worthless.&nbsp; None are accurate over more than a very small scale.&nbsp; If it reads 100% when wrapped in a damp towel, and 80% when in a dry room doesn't surprise me at all.<br /><br />Mist your substrates, and if the water evaporates completely in 20 to 30 minutes, your humidity is OK.&nbsp; If it evaporates after only ten minutes, your area is too dry.&nbsp; If they're still wet after more than 30 minutes, increase fresh air supply.<br /><br />I grow commercially and don't even use hygrometers in my farm, because they're crap these days and I won't waste any more money on them.&nbsp; I judge humidity by the above.<br />RR","title":"Re: How cAn i tell if my hygro is working correctly? (not a calib question really)"}}